# tinystories-transformer - Cursor Rules

## Codebase Map

DATA FLOW (training):
  data/tokenizer.py (TinyStoriesTokenizer)
    -> data/preprocess.py (tokenize -> chunk -> save binary tensors)
    -> data/dataset.py (TinyStoriesDataset, DataLoader)
    -> training/trainer.py (AMP loop)
    -> training/checkpointing.py (save best.pt + latest.pt -> GDrive sync)

DATA FLOW (inference):
  training/checkpointing.py (load_checkpoint)
    -> model/transformer.py (GPTModel)
    -> model/kv_cache.py (KVCache, mode: full/sliding_window/none)
    -> inference/generate.py (autoregressive generation)
    -> inference/chat.py (ChatSession, multi-turn history)

MODEL INTERNALS:
  model/transformer.py (GPTModel) contains TransformerBlock and RMSNorm
  which calls model/attention.py (MultiHeadAttention, KV cache interface)
  Normalization: model/transformer.py RMSNorm (not LayerNorm when enabled)

EXPERIMENT PIPELINE:
  scripts/run_experiments.py
    -> evaluation/rq_experiments.py (run_rq1, run_rq2)
    -> evaluation/metrics.py (perplexity, cache_hit_rate, pearson_r)
    -> results/rq1_results.csv, results/rq2_results.csv

ENTRY POINTS:
  scripts/train.py              - local or Colab training
  scripts/chat_terminal.py      - Windows terminal chat (CUDA RTX 2080)
  scripts/run_experiments.py    - RQ1 + RQ2 experiment sweeps
  notebooks/train_colab.ipynb   - full Colab walkthrough
  notebooks/chat_colab.ipynb    - inference-only Colab notebook

## Coding Rules

1. CONFIG IS THE SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH
   All hyperparameters live in configs/default.yaml loaded via OmegaConf.
   Never hardcode learning rate, batch size, layer counts, or seq_len inside modules.
   CLI flags override config values; never the reverse.

2. DEVICE AGNOSTIC - ALWAYS
   Never call .cuda() unconditionally. Always accept a device argument and
   use tensor.to(device). Auto-detect with:
     device = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')

3. KV CACHE CONTRACT
   Every attention module must accept (kv_cache: Optional[KVCache] = None, layer_idx: int = 0).
   When cache is None: compute fresh. When cache is present: use kv_cache.update().
   Never pass cache=None to the cache object - that's a different thing.

4. AMP DISCIPLINE
   autocast() wraps ONLY the forward pass.
   scaler.scale(loss).backward() for the backward pass.
   scaler.step(optimizer) + scaler.update() for the optimizer step.
   Never wrap optimizer.step() inside autocast.

5. CHECKPOINT SAFETY
   Every checkpoint contains: model_state_dict, optimizer_state_dict,
   scaler_state_dict, step, val_loss, config, timestamp.
   Load all of them on resume - never just model weights.

6. WINDOWS TERMINAL ENCODING
   scripts/chat_terminal.py MUST call sys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')
   before any other output. GPT-2 BPE produces Unicode that kills Windows terminals.

7. VALIDATION WARM-UP
   Do not evaluate val perplexity in the first 100 steps.
   The model is random; the loss is meaningless and wastes time.

8. TOKENIZER IS ALWAYS GPT-2 BPE
   data/tokenizer.py TinyStoriesTokenizer - vocab_size=50257, EOS=50256.
   The old CharTokenizer from the reference repo is NOT used anywhere in this project.

9. NO GLOBAL STATE
   Pass model, tokenizer, device, config explicitly into every function.
   No module-level singletons.

10. REPRODUCIBILITY
    utils/seed.py set_seed(config.training.seed) is called at the top of
    every entry point script before data loading or model init.

## Where to Make Changes

Change model size          -> configs/default.yaml model section
Change KV window           -> configs/default.yaml inference.default_window_size
                             or pass --window_size CLI arg to run_experiments.py
Add a new experiment       -> evaluation/rq_experiments.py, wire into scripts/run_experiments.py
Change LR schedule         -> training/trainer.py cosine_lr()
Debug GPU OOM              -> training/gpu_optimizer.py BatchSizeAutoTuner + memory_log CSV
Switch tokenizer backend   -> data/tokenizer.py TinyStoriesTokenizer.__init__() (tiktoken vs HF)
Change evaluation prompts  -> evaluation/rq_experiments.py RQ1_PROMPTS list at top of file

## Files That Should NOT Be Modified During Experiments
  model/kv_cache.py          - interface is frozen; only window_size changes across experiments
  training/checkpointing.py  - checkpoint format must stay stable across all runs
  data/preprocess.py         - run once, cache to disk, never re-run mid-experiment
  data/tokenizer.py          - tokenizer must not change between preprocess and training
